The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 Madrid, June 29: A week after failing to deflate record oil prices at a summit in Saudi Arabia, the worlds biggest crude producers and consumers will get another chance to tackle the problem at the 19th World Petroleum Congress in Madrid. The meet will be attended by more than 3,000 delegates, including leading corporate and political figures.                            
	 London, June 29: ArcelorMittal CEO Lakshmi Mittal is planning to secure deposits of coal and iron ore to meet the companys demand. Mittal is in talks to acquire coal mines in Australia and Russia, while expansion elsewhere means the steel major now meets 45 per cent of its iron ore requirements from its own supplies, The Observer reported.                            
	 New Delhi, June 29: Videocon-promoted telecom venture Datacoms rollout plans involving an investment of up to Rs 15,000 crore may be upset with its minority shareholder HFCL preparing for a legal battle for the alleged violation of shareholders agreement between the two.                             
	 Mumbai, June 29: Raising non-foodgrain crop output may prove out to be a challenging task for India, the National Council of Applied Economic Research (NCAER) said in its study.                            
	 Mumbai, June 29: Three leading public sector banks  the State Bank of India, Bank of India and Union Bank of India  are getting ready to roll out banking services on cellphones in the coming few weeks.                                                                                                                         
